cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR

The paper discusses the use of retrieval information to improve the presentation of website content, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper also focuses on improving the user's web search experience, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of query trends to dynamically present content also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) to ensure user privacy. Finally, the proposal to give content providers a say in the process of improving content presentation relates to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY).
